<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Casts Cavorting Bones and raises this horse from the dead =P</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Angus[CC]">Angus[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:35 p.m. 8/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Casts Cavorting Bones and raises this horse from the dead =P<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1314" TARGET=_self>Putting down the sick horse</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I agree with Leo. Not much more to say on it that he didn't cover

<P>&gt; There is no reason why there should be an upper attack limit. A
<BR>&gt; player or players should be able to attack those who are 4+ over
<BR>&gt; themselves if they so desire. However there is no good reason to
<BR>&gt; allow the opposite to occur. As far as what limit is used, it
<BR>&gt; could be expanded outward at higher levels. At level 20 increase
<BR>&gt; the spread to 5 levels, at 30 to 6 levels, and at 40 to 7
<BR>&gt; levels. When you hit 50 make it 8 levels so you can attack all
<BR>&gt; the way down to 42. Anything more is just unreasonable.
<P>&gt; You get a lot of character slots in EQ. If someone is talking
<BR>&gt; smack to you, log in your lower level character and put them
<BR>&gt; down, or call your lower level friends to do the job. EQ simply
<BR>&gt; does not support fighting outside the level limits. Finally for
<BR>&gt; groups, my GAR system should be used to allow a broader range of
<BR>&gt; players to fight each other in group vs group, and a group
<BR>&gt; /gduel feature needs to be implemented.
<P>&gt; Now lets let this dead horse rest in peace.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
